      "id": 6,
      "options": {
        "content": "## Signals\n\n- Logs are retained from the UniFi UCG Ultra via a dedicated Vector syslog receiver on `habiki`.\n- Stable Loki labels: `service=unifi-network`, `host=ucg-ultra`, `event_class`, `action`, `severity`, and `protocol`.\n- Structured fields are parsed from retained messages for source and destination IPs, ports, rule context, and threat metadata when present.\n- Current scope: firewall events, threat or IDS events, and warning-or-higher UniFi messages.\n",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "10.0.0",
      "title": "Signal Coverage",
      "transparent": true,
      "type": "text"
    },
